news.title: Indian Bank to wind up Ind Bank Housing after RBI cancels CoR
news.para: Indian Bank MD & CEO S L Jain told reporters in Chennai on Thursday that Ind Bank Housing had not been working for the past two decades.

news.title: BNY Mellon leases over 162,000 sq ft workspace in Pune
news.para: The New York-headquartered company’s latest office is spread across five entire floors at Raheja Woods in one of Pune’s prime commercial zones Kalyani Nagar.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC scraps 'credit note' deal with DBS Realty for PAP tenements
news.para: DBS was to purchase the required land and get its title transferred in the name of BMC before starting construction. BMC commissioner I S Chahal said the developer failed to comply with this condition.

news.title: Sundaram Home Finance posts net profit of Rs 59.33 crore
news.para: ​​For the half-year ending September 30, 2023 the net profit of Sundaram Home Finance grew to Rs 116.75 crore, up by 20 per cent, from Rs 97.56 crore registered during the same period of last year.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth over Rs 70 crore of DHFL promoters
news.para: ​The probe against the Wadhawans pertains to "cheating" a consortium of 17 banks to the tune of Rs 34,615 crore and the money laundering case stems from a Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) FIR, the agency said in a statement.

news.title: Oberoi Realty divests its shareholding in Sangam City Township for Rs 3.60 crore
news.para: The stake, which has been bought by Pune-based Balewadi Techpark, comprised of 9,500 equity share of Rs 10 each, fully paid up.

news.title: Plans for 100% development fees for areas near Pune metro line
news.para: The changes proposed will impact 23 merged villages near the Metro line where the charges will be 1% instead of 0.5%, while for the interior areas the authority has proposed reduction in charges.

news.title: New home sales in US scale 19-month high as median price drops
news.para: A chronic shortage of previously owned houses is driving buyers to new construction, a situation that builders are taking advantage of by giving a range of incentives to improve affordability.

news.title: Mumbai: Vasai man who posed as builder, cheated prospective buyers arrested
news.para: Sumit Dube’s modus operandi was to advertise the sale of flats in new and old buildings in the Vasai region on social media platforms.

news.title: Chinese asset managers apply to launch first commercial property-backed REITs
news.para: China's securities regulator expanded the REITs scheme to include consumer-related commercial properties, such as shopping malls and department stores, as part of the government's efforts to help the ailing real estate market.

news.title: Home First Finance Company's net profit increases by 36.91% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Home First Finance Company's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 277.98 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 46.77 per cent from Rs 189.40 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Gurugram: Nod for boom barriers, gates to four colonies
news.para: The department had received applications from the residents of Brahma City, DLF Pink Town House U block, Sushant Lok 1 A block, Rosewood City A block and Sector 60.

news.title: Udaipur Cement Works posts net profit of Rs 12.15 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Udaipur Cement Works' net total income stood at Rs 269.52 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 22.23 per cent from Rs 220.50 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Embassy REIT's net profit increases by 68.67% in Q2 FY24
news.para: The board of directors of Embassy Office Parks Management Services, manager to Embassy REIT, declared distributions of Rs 524.18 crore / Rs 5.53 per unit for the quarter ended September 30, 2023.

news.title: Asian Paints' net profit up 53.31% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Asian Paints' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 8,643.77 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 1.06 per cent from Rs 8,553.04 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Noida: 171 GRAP violations, Rs 43 lakh fines issued since October 1
news.para: ​The figures were shared during a review meeting called by Noida Authority's Chief Executive Officer Lokesh M to discuss the compliance of orders issued in the previous meeting.

news.title: ACC posts net profit of Rs 387.88 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: ACC's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 4,644.78 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 14.49 per cent from Rs 4,057.08 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ganesh Housing Corporation to develop IT SEZ with investment of Rs 8,000 crore in Ahmedabad
news.para: Ganesh Housing Corporation, in collaboration with US real estate development and investment firm Tishman Speyer, the SEZ, called “Million Minds Tech City”, will come up on 65 acres near Chharodi village along SG Road in Ahmedabad.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers approves issue of NCDs worth Rs 113.65 crore
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers recorded sales value of Rs 1,333 crore during H1 FY24 as compared to Rs 812 crore in H1 FY23, marking a growth of 64% year-on-year.

news.title: Two government offices pay Rs 4 crore property tax to Nashik civic body
news.para: According to NMC officials, the civic body recovered taxes from two offices, including one central government office which has signed an agreement with the NMC saying it would pay service charge instead of property tax.
